# 🎓 Bachelor Contents Repository

This repository contains a structured collection of materials from my Bachelor's studies in **Electrical and Electronics Engineering**.

It serves as both:
- 📚 a personal knowledge base
- 🧠 a revision resource
- 💼 a portfolio demonstrating academic and technical development

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

The repository is organized into different subject areas and course contents, including:

- 📡 Signal Processing & Communication
- ⚡ Electronics & Circuit Design
- 🧮 Mathematics & Linear Algebra
- 💻 Embedded Systems & Programming
- 🤖 Machine Learning & Data Analysis
- 📊 Projects, Assignments, and Notes

Each folder typically includes:
- Lecture notes
- Assignments / solutions
- Supporting documents
- Code implementations (when applicable)

---

## 🎯 Purpose

This repository is designed to:

- Keep all academic materials organized in one place  
- Enable quick revision before exams  
- Track learning progress over time  
- Share useful resources with others  
- Showcase technical background for internships / graduate applications  

---

## 🛠️ Technologies & Tools

Throughout this repository, the following tools and technologies are used:

- MATLAB / Simulink  
- Python (NumPy, SciPy, Matplotlib)  
- Embedded C / Microcontrollers  
- Git & Version Control  
- LabView

